# ERS Portugal Content Compliance

This rule ensures all user-facing content aligns with Portuguese health regulatory requirements (ERS - Entidade Reguladora da Saúde) for digital health platforms providing telemedicine services.

## Core Principle

Eleva.care operates as a **digital health platform** (plataforma digital de saúde) that enables remote healthcare services by independent professionals. The platform does NOT provide clinical care itself.

## Required Platform Identity

**Always use:**

```
EN: "digital health platform"
ES: "plataforma digital de salud"
PT: "plataforma digital de saúde"
PT-BR: "plataforma digital de saúde"
```

**Never use:**

- "marketplace" / "mercado de saúde" / "marketplace de salud"
- "healthcare marketplace"
- "we are not a healthcare provider" (as standalone identity)
- "not a clinic" / "no somos clínica" / "não somos clínica"
- "only a technology platform"
- "limited to technology only"

## Canonical Platform Description

Use this structure consistently across all locales:

```
EN: "Eleva.care is a digital health platform that enables the delivery of remote
    healthcare services (teleconsultations / telemedicine) by independent,
    licensed professionals."

ES: "Eleva.care es una plataforma digital de salud que permite la prestación de
    servicios de salud remotos (teleconsultas / telemedicina) por profesionales
    independientes y licenciados."

PT: "A Eleva.care é uma plataforma digital de saúde que permite a prestação de
    serviços de saúde remotos (teleconsultas / telemedicina) por profissionais
    independentes e licenciados."

PT-BR: "A Eleva.care é uma plataforma digital de saúde que permite a prestação de
       serviços de saúde remotos (teleconsultas / telemedicina) por profissionais
       independentes e licenciados."
```

## Responsibility Separation

### Platform Responsibilities (Eleva.care)

Always acknowledge organizational, technical, and administrative duties:

```
EN: "Eleva.care assumes organizational, technical, and administrative responsibility
    for operating the digital health platform, in accordance with applicable
    Portuguese and EU regulations."

ES: "Eleva.care asume responsabilidad organizativa, técnica y administrativa por
    la operación de la plataforma digital de salud, de conformidad con la
    legislación portuguesa y de la Unión Europea aplicable."

PT: "A Eleva.care assume responsabilidade organizacional, técnica e administrativa
    pela operação da plataforma digital de saúde, em conformidade com a legislação
    portuguesa e da União Europeia aplicável."
```

### Expert Responsibilities (Clinical)

Experts are solely responsible for clinical care:

```
EN: "Experts are solely responsible for clinical decisions, patient outcomes, and
    maintaining required insurance."

ES: "Los especialistas son exclusivamente responsables de las decisiones clínicas,
    resultados de los pacientes y de mantener el seguro requerido."

PT: "Os especialistas são exclusivamente responsáveis pelas decisões clínicas,
    resultados dos pacientes e por manter o seguro exigido."
```

## Clinical Non-Interference

Always clarify that Eleva does NOT interfere with clinical judgment:

```
EN: "Eleva.care does not provide clinical care or medical treatment. We do not
    employ experts and do not interfere with or supervise their clinical judgment."

ES: "Eleva.care no presta atención clínica ni tratamiento médico. No empleamos
    especialistas y no interferimos ni supervisamos su juicio clínico."

PT: "A Eleva.care não presta cuidados clínicos nem tratamento médico. Não
    empregamos especialistas e não interferimos nem supervisionamos o seu
    julgamento clínico."
```

## Credential Verification Language

Use balanced language showing diligence without overstating:

**✅ CORRECT:**

```
EN: "Experts self-declare their credentials and professional status. Eleva.care
    may request documentation and perform reasonable checks where required for
    platform integrity, regulatory compliance, or risk management."

ES: "Los especialistas autodeclaran sus credenciales y estatus profesional.
    Eleva.care puede solicitar documentación y realizar verificaciones razonables
    cuando sea necesario para la integridad de la plataforma, el cumplimiento
    normativo o la gestión de riesgos."

PT: "Os especialistas auto-declaram as suas credenciais e estatuto profissional.
    A Eleva.care pode solicitar documentação e efetuar verificações razoáveis
    quando necessário para integridade da plataforma, conformidade regulamentar
    ou gestão de risco."
```

**❌ NEVER USE:**

- "All experts are verified" (overstates verification)
- "We verify all credentials" (implies active verification)
- "We don't verify credentials" (no diligence shown)
- "Fully vetted professionals"

## Evidence-Based Care Claims

When discussing clinical protocols or evidence:

**✅ CORRECT:**

```
"The platform supports evidence-based practices aligned with international
guidelines and peer-reviewed research. Experts maintain clinical independence
and follow escalation pathways when appropriate."
```

**❌ NEVER USE:**

- "We follow clinical protocols" (implies clinical supervision)
- "Our clinical team reviews" (implies clinical control)
- "We ensure quality of care" (implies clinical responsibility)

## Governing Law & Language Precedence

All legal documents must include:

```
EN: "These Terms are governed by Portuguese law. Courts in Portugal have
    jurisdiction over disputes."

    "In case of divergence between language versions, the Portuguese version
    shall prevail."

PT-BR: "Em caso de divergência entre versões linguísticas, prevalece a versão
       em português de Portugal." (Note: specifically "de Portugal" for PT-BR)
```

**Never reference local laws (Brazilian/Spanish) for clinical matters.**

## Red Flags Checklist

Before committing content changes, verify:

- [ ] No "marketplace" terminology
- [ ] No standalone "not a healthcare provider" identity claims
- [ ] No absolute verification claims ("all experts verified")
- [ ] No clinical supervision language ("we follow protocols", "we ensure care")
- [ ] Platform responsibilities acknowledged (organizational, technical, administrative)
- [ ] Expert clinical responsibilities clearly stated
- [ ] Portuguese law governance included in legal docs
- [ ] Language precedence disclaimer present (PT version prevails)
- [ ] No local law references for clinical matters (no Brazilian/Spanish law)

## File-Specific Guidelines

### Legal MDX Files (`src/content/terms/`, `src/content/expert-agreement/`, etc.)

- Must include Definitions section with canonical terms
- Must include Portuguese law governance clause
- Must include language precedence disclaimer
- Must maintain parallel structure across all 4 locales

### Messages JSON (`src/messages/*.json`)

- Platform disclaimers must use "digital health platform"
- Expert disclaimers must mention "self-certify" + "may request documentation"
- Notification keys should use "platform" not "marketplace"

### Marketing Content (`src/content/about/`, `src/content/evidence-based-care/`)

- Avoid overstating verification or clinical oversight
- Use "platform supports" not "we follow" for clinical references
- Emphasize expert independence and clinical autonomy

### Email Templates (`src/emails/`)

- No marketplace terminology in payment/payout emails
- Platform framing consistent with legal documents

